Ivor J. Evans  Independent Director, Textron Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 16 different industries.See Board Relationships75$257,500
Background

		Mr. Ivor J. Evans, also known as Ike, served as an Executive Chairman of Meritor, Inc. from May 3, 2013 to April 2016. Mr. Evans served as an Operating Partner at HCI Equity Partners since April 2005. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Meritor, Inc. from August 9, 2013 to March 2015. He served as the President of Meritor, Inc. from May 3, 2013 to June 9, 2014. He served as Interim Chief Executive Officer of Meritor, Inc. since May 3, 2013 until August 9, 2013. ... He served as the President of Valeo Engine Cooling, Inc. He served as President and Chief Operating Officer of Union Pacific Railroad Company from September 1998 to 2004 and was responsible for the day-to-day operations, marketing and sales functions of the company. He joined Union Pacific in 1998. He served as an Executive at Motors Liquidation Company. He served as Senior Vice President of Industrial Components and Equipment at Emerson Electric Co. from 1989 to 1998. He served as President of the Blackstone Corporation. He began his career at General Motors Corporation, where he spent 21 years holding a number of key operating positions in the Chevrolet, Buick, Delco Products and Harrison Radiator divisions. He serves as the Chairman of Dynamic Systems Inc. He served as the Chairman of the Association of American Railroads and the National Association of Manufacturers.  He served as the Chairman of Suntron Corporation since November 2005. He served as the Chairman of Roadrunner Transportation Systems, Inc. from July 2008 to March 2010. He served as Vice Chairman of Suntron Corporation from May 11, 2005 to November 2005. He served as the Vice Chairman of Union Pacific Corporation and Union Pacific Railroad Company from January 2004 to March 2005. He has been Director of Suntron Corporation since May 11, 2005. He has been a Director of Meritor, Inc. since May 31, 2005. He has been a Director of Roadrunner Transportation Services, Inc. since March 2005 and Spirit AeroSystems, Inc. since July 18, 2005. He has been an Independent Director of Textron Inc. since July 28, 2003. He serves as a Director of Power & Composite Technologies Inc.; Total Quality, Inc.; and Group Transportation Services, Inc. He served as a of Roadrunner Transportation Systems, Inc. from March 2005 to April 3, 2014. He served as a Director of Spirit AeroSystems Holdings, Inc. since November 15, 2006 until April 22, 2015. He served as a Director of Union Pacific Corporation and Union Pacific Railroad Company from 1999 to February 2005. He served as a Director of Cooper Industries plc since April 29, 2003 to 2012. He served as a Director of Union Pacific, Grupo Ferroviario Mexicano, Creighton University of Omaha. He has 40 years of experience in industrial manufacturing, logistics and the automotive industry. Mr. Evans earned a Bachelor’s degree in Electrical Engineering at Kansas State University and completed the Management Development program at Harvard University.Read Full Background




